{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.27",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 27 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:1",
      "text": "And Job further continued and said in his parable,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:2",
      "text": "As God lives, who has thus judged me; and the Almighty, who has embittered my soul;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:3",
      "text": "verily, while my breath is yet in me, and the breath of God which remains to me is in my nostrils,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:4",
      "text": "my lips shall not speak evil words, neither shall my soul meditate unrighteous thoughts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:5",
      "text": "Far be it from me that I should justify you till I die; for I will not let go my innocence,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:6",
      "text": "but keeping fast to my righteousness I will by no means let it go: for I am not conscious to myself of having done any thing amiss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:7",
      "text": "Nay rather, but let mine enemies be as the overthrow of the ungodly, and they that rise up against me, as the destruction of transgressors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:8",
      "text": "For what is the hope of the ungodly, that he holds to it? will he indeed trust in the Lord and be saved?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:9",
      "text": "Will God hear his prayer? or, when distress has come upon him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:10",
      "text": "has he any confidence before him? or will God hear him as he calls upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:11",
      "text": "Yet now I will tell you what is in the hand of the Lord: I will not lie concerning the things which are with the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:12",
      "text": "Behold, ye all know that ye are adding vanity to vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:13",
      "text": "This is the portion of an ungodly man from the Lord, and the possession of oppressors shall come upon them from the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:14",
      "text": "And if their children be many, they shall be for slaughter: and if they grow up, they shall beg.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:15",
      "text": "And they that survive of him shall utterly perish, and no one shall pity their widows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:16",
      "text": "Even if he should gather silver as earth, and prepare gold as clay;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:17",
      "text": "all these things shall the righteous gain, and the truehearted shall possess his wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:18",
      "text": "And his house is gone like moths, and like a spider's web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:19",
      "text": "The rich man shall lie down, and shall not continue: he has opened his eyes, and he is not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:20",
      "text": "Pains have come upon him as water, and darkness has carried him away by night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:21",
      "text": "And a burning wind shall catch him, and he shall depart, and it shall utterly drive him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:22",
      "text": "And God shall cast trouble upon him, and not spare: he would fain flee out of his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.27.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:23",
      "text": "He shall cause men to clap their hands against them, and shall hiss him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
